caption: Typical Parisian theater. Hidden in a building but well known by the locals. Might need some renovations though.
Very uncomfortable seats

Small theater on a human scale which allows you to be close to the actors and the stage. On the other hand, sitting on chairs with a backrest is very uncomfortable. You come out with a terrible neck ache from having to struggle to raise your head to see the scene. This reflection was unanimous among the public. It ruined the room. Very damaging.
Very nice piece. Franck Le Boeuf is really surprising as an actor and the 3 other actors are very talented. We've already seen the first one, I hope there will be more.
Disconcertingly dilapidated, suffocating heat, the room is absolutely not ventilated!!! A complete renovation is required as soon as possible.  Nonetheless, good programming. I had a great time.

A fantastic place for a moving comedy! The room is superb: You have room to put your legs, you are seated very comfortably and there are plenty of seats. As for the comedy that I saw there (my best friend) I really loved it, I had lots of laughs and I have excellent memories of it!

Very nice theater, the room is rather large, the price is affordable, but it still depends on the show. I went to see “when China will call”, and I found it very good, I recommend it! A very nice little theater, where you can visit from time to time to have a good evening.
The magnificent spectacle. The seats should be changed immediately.

Good evening, I love this place, it's magnificent and I love the theater... I would like to come forward to see... frankly very good reputation, I congratulate you.... see you very soon, I look forward to it... excellent evening. ..

The atmosphere of a Parisian theater, small room located in an area with many restaurants and bars...very good evening, but I do not recommend the balcony seats, the seats are not at all comfortable, especially when you do more '1m80... And visibility can be a little complicated on stage...
We went to see: hello drunkenness, very pleasant, light and friendly piece! Very pretty old theater, uncomfortable seats, it's a little cold in winter!

We arrived at 8:46 p.m. for the Zize show which started at 8:45 p.m.  When we saw us, the ticket clerk quickly pulled the curtain, categorically refusing to give us the invitation tickets. The manager also refused to let 3 of us in, but just accepts 2 people. In short, we didn't understand their madness. The staff are fundamentally racist. In short, a theater to avoid.
A good performance hall but with limited seats and no escape in the event of fire or otherwise when the folding seats are used, we are far from the obligatory standards. They seem to be used often...
Very friendly and accommodating staff. The play that was playing is called Model Parents, we had an excellent evening. It’s a Parisian theater “in its own right”
Room and interior communications to renovate. Review the seat spacing! Adults stay away from the balcony! Average to poor visibility depending on placement. Uncomfortable seat. It's a shame...
Great room but a bit dated theater and not very comfortable seating. The evening was good all the same!
Too small no air conditioning Unfortunately, although the play is nice, it is so hot that we can't concentrate. Damage
Very poor comfort: space so small that I have to spread my legs around the front backrest (1m76). It's 30°. Poor visibility. Moldy walls. I advise against it.
I took our tickets for June and the session was canceled so I'm taking another date for July 5 at 9 p.m. What's not our surprise!!! Closed doors. It's unacceptable. No one warned us. It's shameful.

Small theater near the Olympia. Old seats but a great show and perfect for small budgets. Do not miss under any circumstances... Zize in the mamamia family... Delirious for 1h15... Don't forget your tissues...
Superb play. We laugh from start to finish. Thanks to the actors. See you soon on stage in a new interpretation. Thank you again for this fantastic moment
We had a good evening there. Great programming. The theater could use a little renovation.

Make life good at the Comédie Caumartin, the whole team is really charming, we are well received there, good plays are programmed... We went to see Ma Belle Mère my Ex and I and we cried with laughter!! A good outing in this small Parisian theater, full of charm... a stone's throw from the Opéra Garnier! Ideal !
Very good “little” theater! Room overheated but nothing annoying! Avoid the front row too close to the stage
The place could do with a little refreshment, both in terms of cleaning (lots of dust on the curtains) and in terms of the quality of the seats... But it was a very pleasant and entertaining show.
Parisian theater par excellence, decent room but quite unbearable heat in summer... The investment in air conditioning would be a real plus.
Beautiful and good theater as we like them, warm, comfortable and giving additional pleasure to the play we come to see.
Charming Parisian theater. The seats are certainly old-fashioned but no matter where we are placed, we can see the actors very clearly.
It wouldn't be a luxury to change the folding seats! We are not sitting but semi-lying in an uncomfortable position. Luckily the piece was great.
Comfort in this theater can be improved. The visibility of the stage is very dependent on the position in the room
A nice place, a small room which allows you to be close to the artists who are representing themselves. A little old-fashioned but like many performance halls in Paris.
Small theater full of surprises and which schedules, among other things, an evening where laughter and derision are on the agenda that you have to go see: Absolutely Hilarious 1 Monday out of 2
This place is magnificent and what we see there is always very beautiful. It is, after all, a small theater.
Model parents. A dynamic comedy where the laughter is permanent and crescendo. The originality of the staging allows for an avalanche of characters, played by only 2 explosive actors. To have...
Nice place. ..but the places at the ends of the rows do not allow you to follow the pieces correctly because of the curtains. .we don't see the artists on the sides.
Small, very friendly theater, lack of comfort in the seats (barely padded board)
Slightly old theater, seats worn out but the plays to see are good and the area is nice for an evening
A must-see piece, my best friend. A great hilarious moment. Nice little theater.
